But wait - the original baseline worked fine! Let me think about why... The original test run DID work. Let me check if maybe the global.json was being used to pin the SDK before. Let me look at what the global.json says:

```json
{
  "test": {
    "runner": "VSTest"
  }
}
```

It doesn't pin the SDK. So the baseline used SDK 10.0.201 as well and it built just fine. 

Let me test if removing the `OutputType=Exe` setting resolves this - that might be the actual culprit rather than the package updates themselves.
